payload: FYI, please also know that if the change is simply a meter change, that does not effect the value. Only the Pipeline and trading zone will effect the value. Thanks again. PL ---------------------- Forwarded by Phillip M Love/HOU/ECT on 01/30/2001 02:10 PM --------------------------- Phillip M Love 01/30/2001 02:03 PM To: George F Smith/HOU/ECT@ECT cc: Subject: changing deal locations I have a favor to ask. Would you mind asking your team to email or phone me when they make a location change on a deal in sitara. We had a case yesterday where a deal was originally entered at one location for the deal and for the hedge. The point was incorrect and a person in logistics corrected it. The problem occurs in that sitara looks to verify the locations are the same on the deal and the hedge and if they are, it will then value the deal in the trader's book at mid. If the locations are different, it will value the deal at the customer price. This could potentially have a large impact on the trader's P&L. It does not seem pertinent to have your guys changing swap locations in addition to changing deal locations due to time constraints. We will be more than happy to make the changes, and we should also be able to catch these problems in the first place when we calc our books. I would greatly appreciate your groups help in cutting some of these issues off at the pass. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to give me a shout. Thanks. PL
entity_list: 'Phillip M Love' : 'person', 'Phillip M Love' : 'person', 'George F Smith' : 'person'
Subject: changing deal locations

PL Elizabeth L Hernandez 12/05/2000 03:09 PM To: Phillip M Love/HOU/ECT@ECT cc: Charles Jacobs/NA/Enron@Enron Subject: Consumers Energy You entered these deals in Sitara. Could you please get with Chuck Jacobs to resolve this issue. Please see his e mail. ---------------------- Forwarded by Elizabeth L Hernandez/HOU/ECT on 12/05/2000 03:08 PM --------------------------- From: Charles Jacobs @ ENRON 12/05/2000 12:59 PM To: Elizabeth L Hernandez/HOU/ECT@ECT cc: Subject: Consumers Energy Elizabeth, Can you check out Deal #'s 411921 (Sale) and 411937 (Purchase)? Looks like a buy/sell where we sold to Consumers Energy in October (1,000,000 total at 5.20) and bought it back from them in November. Both deals have 0 rates so that's not a problem. The problem is - there's an exchange fee on both deals of $0.0725. But it's a negative fee on the sales side and a positive fee on the purchase side. That means I would owe them a netted amount of $145,000. Is that right?? Should the sale side maybe be positive so the two sides net to 0 - or do we owe them this money?? Also, the confirmation

payload: FYI, please also know that if the change is simply a meter change, that does not effect the value. Only the Pipeline and trading zone will effect the value. Thanks again. PL ---------------------- Forwarded by Phillip M Love/HOU/ECT on 01/30/2001 02:10 PM --------------------------- Phillip M Love 01/30/2001 02:03 PM To: George F Smith/HOU/ECT@ECT cc: Subject: changing deal locations I have a favor to ask. Would you mind asking your team to email or phone me when they make a location change on a deal in sitara. We had a case yesterday where a deal was originally entered at one location for the deal and for the hedge. The point was incorrect and a person in logistics corrected it. The problem occurs in that sitara looks to verify the locations are the same on the deal and the hedge and if they are, it will then value the deal in the trader's book at mid. If the locations are different, it will value the deal at the customer price. This could potentially have a large impact on the trader's P&L. It does not seem pertinent to have your guys changing swap locations in addition to changing deal locations due to time constraints. We will be more than happy to make the changes, and we should also be able to catch these problems in the first place when we calc our books. I would greatly appreciate your groups help in cutting some of these issues off at the pass. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to give me a shout. Thanks. PL
entity_list: 'Phillip M Love' : 'person', 'Phillip M Love' : 'person', 'George F Smith' : 'person'
Subject: changing deal locations

payload: Phillip, I spoke with someone in our technical team about the ability to provide the EnronOnline price reports in a downloadable format. What I think we can do is send a csv file (comma separated values) to the O:\ drive everyday containing all of the data that appears in the EnronOnline price reports. Then, you could just go in and open that it in Excel or copy and paste it from the csv file into Excel, which is easy. Let me know if I can explain this better. As far as saving it on the O:\ drive is concerned, I am currently thinking that we would just create a new folder that EOL can access and you can access. This way, if any other desk has a similar request to yours, they can just get permission to access that folder. We are going to finalize the details, and I will let you know how long it will take to get this done. The technical person who can do it is out of the office until Thursday, so I am assuming we won't have a good estimate until then. I will keep you posted. Thank you. payload: I will play if the street thug doesn't Phillip M Love 03/30/2000 02:29 PM To: Eric Bass/HOU/ECT@ECT, David Baumbach/HOU/ECT@ECT, Kevin Bosse/HOU/ECT@ECT, Bryan Hull/HOU/ECT@ECT, Gregg Lenart/HOU/ECT@ECT, Eric Wardle/HOU/ECT@ECT, B Scott Palmer/HOU/ECT@ECT, O'Neal D Winfree/HOU/ECT@ECT, Drew Hill/HOU/ECT@ECT, Jimmy Simien/Corp/Enron@ENRON, Mark Feldman/HOU/ECT@ECT cc: Subject: softball I wanted to take a minute to apologize to you guys for the scene at last night's game. I did not do a captain's job of controlling the situation, and I am sorry. That being said, I am writing to determine if we will have a team in the next session. We had previously committed to play, but with recent developments, I am not sure if everyone is still interested. Please let me know if you will be interested in playing in the next session because I have already told the sportsplex that we will be playing. If we decide not to play, I need to let them know ASAP and try and get the money back(forfeit deposit). It is critical that I get a 100% response to this email to gauge whether or not we have enough people. Due to the increased number of the people on the team working in risk, we will need as many bodies as possible due to the early games this session(they start this time at 6:30). The season begins next
